description:
Use this shield if you want a little more protection 
than knocking on wood.
name: Wooden Shield

description: It keeps the sweat out of your eyes. Fight! Fight!
name: Headband

description:
Comfortable, lightweight clothes. They don't provide 
much protection from blows.
name: Casual Clothes

description:
These probably aren't real hairs from the god of fire, 
but his power still flows through this necklace.
name: Hair of Kresnik

description:
A reinforced steel shield. Only Fran thinks it looks 
like a cookie.
name: Round Shield

description:
It gets a bit sweaty, but the protection is definitely 
worth it.
name: Leather Vest

description:
A shiny shirt that feels good on the skin. Look rich 
while you're being protected.
name: Silk Shirt

description:
A vest made from the scales of some unlucky monster. 
It feels wonderfully smooth to the touch.
name: Scale Vest

description:
This cloak is part of the Hero's Dragon-slaying series 
of items. Absorbs fire like it's nothing.
name: Dragon Cloak

description:
A fancy silk hat. If this was a different game, it'd 
help keep you sane.
name: Silk Hat

description:
It makes you look and feel super cute. Weirdly enough, 
your hearing will get better when wearing these.
name: Cat Ears

description:
A lot more sturdy than you'd expect. Fran can't 
recognise any of the flowers on here.
name: Flower Crown

description:
This circlet is part of the Hero's Dragon-slaying 
series of items. Protects from a little magic.
name: Dragon Circlet

description:
Made with a responsibly-sourced turtle shell. It might 
reflect a little water damage.
name: Turtle Shield

description:
It's a soft and squishy teddy bear. Enemies will target 
the user more often.
name: Fat Plushie

description:
A dazzling, iridescent shield. Reflects some magic 
damage back to the enemy.
name: Prism Shield

description:
A heavy iron shield. You could hide your whole body 
behind it. Reduces attack speed and critical evasion.
name: Iron Shield

description:
A large knight's shield that has gone out of fashion. 
Thankfully, being safe is never out of fashion.
name: Pavise

description:
Made from the dense bones of a leviathan-class predator 
from a faraway place. Extremely heavy.
name: Heavy Bone Shield

description:
An oversized shield that is slightly lighter than its 
peers. Blindingly shiny.
name: Platinum Shield

description:
This shield is very expensive and very shiny. Testing 
shows that it absorbs 99%(?) of damage.
name: Knight's Shield

description:
Pieces of leather on the body are better protection 
than having absolutely nothing.
name: Leather Plate

description:
This breastplate will help steel you against the 
dangers of the wilds.
name: Steel Plate

description:
A light bone breatplate. Guaranteed to make you bring 
out your inner warrior.
name: Bone Plate

description:
A fighter's dream. This breastplate will absorb a little 
magic when you get hit, guaranteed.
name: Mithril Plate

description:
The scales of an unlucky dragon were used to create 
this light armour. Absorbs a lot of fire damage.
name: Dragon Plate

description:
Most knights start off wearing this heavy chain armour. 
Frumpy, but effective.
name: Chain Mail

description: Hammered to perfection and fitted instantly, somehow.
name: Steel Armour

description:
Wind gecko scales were used to make this suit of 
armour. Each scale is a different colour.
name: Scale Mail

description:
Orichalcum is known for its hardness and even heat 
distribution. Some use it for pots instead of armour.
name: Orichalcum Armour
note:
special effect
lower eva and atk spd

description:
Waste not, want not. All parts of a dragon can be made 
into exorbitantly expensive items.
name: Dragon Bone Mail

description:
The grounding power of the earth can be carried in your 
pocket for protection. Aids defence.
name: Clay Charm

description:
This crystal lets the dangers of nature pass right through 
you! Reduces the chance of status effects.
name: Vine Crystal

description:
Pegasi are territorial, aggressive creatures. This 
feather was hard to get. Aids speed and evasion.
name: Pegasus Feather

description:
The goddess Ninlil is whimsical, but the best way to 
tie this knot is to be methodical. Aids luck.
name: Ninlil's Knot

description:
This particular shape of cross is the symbol of the 
goddess Fulgora. Aids criticals and experience.
name: Glittering Cross

description:
This ring once belonged to a vampire queen from a 
faraway land. Restores HP and aids all stats.
name: Glowing Ring
note: hp regen accessory, ups all stats

description:
Ravens have long been considered servants of the gods. 
Aids evasion, hit rate and TP gain.
name: Raven's Eye
note: up eva, tp regen, hit rate accessory

description:
The maker of this watch was persecuted for being able 
to destroy divine power. Reduces elemental effects.
name: Pocket Watch

description:
The stone on this pendant reflects no light whatsoever. 
Aids attack but reduces defence and evasion.
name: Shadow Pendant

description:
The safest shield in existence. Captain Safety's legacy 
that nobody wanted. Allows for counterattacks.
name: Safety Shield
